ZCZC EE18
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
MONDAY TO THURSDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE COASTGUARD AND
MARITIME AGENCY AT 252300 UTC
THROUGH MONDAY EVENING AND TUESDAY A DEEP AREA OF LOW
PRESSURE WILL LIE TO THE NE OF ICELAND WITH ACTIVE
FRONTAL TROUGHS EXTENDING ACROSS THE UK. PRESSURE WILL BE
HIGH OVER SERN EUROPE AND IN MID ATLANTIC. THE HIGH
CENTRE WILL MOV EWARDS TO LIE NEAR IRELAND BY THE END OF
TUESDAY. PRESSURE WILL BUILD ACROSS THE UK ON TUESDAY
BEFORE THE CENTRE MOVS INTO THE N SEA LATER. A DEEP AREA
OF LOW PRESSURE WILL FORM IN MID-ATLANTIC. PRESSURE WILL
FALL SLWY OVER THE UK ON THURSDAY WITH HIGH PRESSURE OVER
DENMARK. S OR SW WINDS WILL BE STRG AT FIRST IN FITZROY
SOLE LUNDY FASTNET IRISH SEA AND SHANNON AND OCNL
STRG IN THAMES AND DOVER. STRG NE WINDS MAY DEVELOP LATER
IN SOLE IRISH SEA FASTNET AND SHANNON. ON WEDNESDAY
STRG SE WINDS WILL DEVELOP IN SHANNON AND PERSIST
THROUGH THURSDAY. ON THURSDAY S WINDS WILL BECOME STRG IN
FITZROY SOLE LUNDY FASTNET IRISH SEA
NNNN